This paper discusses the application of Model Agnostic Meta Learning (MAML) to Federated Learning (FL) for personalized model training. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these fields are closely related to FL and MAML. The paper also discusses the use of FL for data created on mobile phones, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language) for natural language processing on mobile devices. Finally, the paper mentions the optimization of a model for a heterogeneous distribution of tasks, which could relate to cs.SY (Systems and Control) for optimizing distributed systems.
